workflow.name: Extract clean transcripts from your YouTube channel videos using Data API
workflow.description:
**YouTube Caption Extractor** *(Your Channel Only)*
Extracts clean transcripts from **YOUR CHANNEL** YouTube video captions using YouTube Data API v3.

**‚ö†Ô∏è API Limitation**: Only works with videos from **YOUR OWN CHANNEL**. Cannot access external/public videos.

---

### üéØ **Use Cases**
- AI summarization & sentiment analysis
- Keyword extraction from your content
- Content generation from your videos
- Batch transcript processing

---

### üîÑ **How It Works** *(6 Steps)*

1. **üì• Input**: Receives `videoId` + `preferredLanguage`
2. **üîç API**: Lists captions from **your channel**
3. **üÜî Selector**: Picks preferred language (fallback to first)
4. **üì• Download**: Gets VTT subtitle file
5. **üßπ Cleaning**: Removes timestamps, [Music], duplicates
6. **‚úÖ Output**: Clean transcript + metadata

---

### üöÄ **How to Use**
* Trigger with JSON payload: `{"youtubeVideoId": "YOUR_VIDEO_ID", "preferredLanguage": "es"}`
* **Video ID must belong to your authenticated YouTube channel**
* Works as sub-workflow (Execute Workflow Trigger) or replace with Webhook/Form trigger
* Handles videos with no captions gracefully with structured error response
* Output ready for downstream AI processing or storage

**‚ö†Ô∏è Setup Required**:
- **Change YouTube credentials** in **"List Captions"** and **"Download VTT"** nodes
- Video ID from **your authenticated channel**
- Sub-workflow or Webhook trigger
- Graceful no-captions handling

---

### üîß **Requirements**
- ‚úÖ YouTube OAuth2 (`youtube.captions.read` scope)
- ‚úÖ **Update credentials** in List Captions + Download VTT nodes
- ‚úÖ n8n HTTP Request + Code nodes

---

### üí¨ **Need Help?**
- [n8n Forum](https://community.n8n.io/)

**Happy Automating! üéâ**

parameters.content:
## üöÄ Try It Out!

### **YouTube Caption Extractor** *(Your Channel Only)*
Extracts clean transcripts from **YOUR CHANNEL** YouTube video captions using YouTube Data API v3.

**‚ö†Ô∏è API Limitation**: Only works with videos from **YOUR OWN CHANNEL**. Cannot access external/public videos.

---

### üéØ **Use Cases**
- AI summarization & sentiment analysis
- Keyword extraction from your content
- Content generation from your videos
- Batch transcript processing

---

### üîÑ **How It Works** *(6 Steps)*

1. **üì• Input**: Receives `videoId` + `preferredLanguage`
2. **üîç API**: Lists captions from **your channel**
3. **üÜî Selector**: Picks preferred language (fallback to first)
4. **üì• Download**: Gets VTT subtitle file
5. **üßπ Cleaning**: Removes timestamps, [Music], duplicates
6. **‚úÖ Output**: Clean transcript + metadata

---

### üöÄ **How to Use**
* Trigger with JSON payload: `{"youtubeVideoId": "YOUR_VIDEO_ID", "preferredLanguage": "es"}`
* **Video ID must belong to your authenticated YouTube channel**
* Works as sub-workflow (Execute Workflow Trigger) or replace with Webhook/Form trigger
* Handles videos with no captions gracefully with structured error response
* Output ready for downstream AI processing or storage

**‚ö†Ô∏è Setup Required**:
- **Change YouTube credentials** in **"List Captions"** and **"Download VTT"** nodes
- Video ID from **your authenticated channel**
- Sub-workflow or Webhook trigger
- Graceful no-captions handling

---

### üîß **Requirements**
- ‚úÖ YouTube OAuth2 (`youtube.captions.read` scope)
- ‚úÖ **Update credentials** in List Captions + Download VTT nodes
- ‚úÖ n8n HTTP Request + Code nodes

---

### üí¨ **Need Help?**
- [n8n Forum](https://community.n8n.io/)

**Happy Automating! üéâ**

## 1. Input Processing
‚Ä¢ Captures workflow execution trigger
‚Ä¢ Sets youtubeVideoId and preferredLanguage variables
‚Ä¢ Passes structured data to YouTube API calls

Example input:
{
  "youtubeVideoId": "nxub8Bmia68",
  "preferredLanguage": "es"
}

## 2. API Discovery & Validation

‚Ä¢ Lists all available captions for the video
‚Ä¢ Checks if captions exist (items.length > 0)
‚Ä¢ Branches to success (TRUE) or fallback (FALSE)
‚Ä¢ YouTube API: captions.list endpoint

Requires YouTube OAuth2 with:
‚Ä¢ youtube.force-ssl
‚Ä¢ youtube.captions.read

## 3. Transcript Processing

‚Ä¢ Downloads VTT caption file
‚Ä¢ Extracts plain text from binary VTT
‚Ä¢ Advanced cleaning removes:
  ‚Ä¢ Timestamps (00:01:23.456,00:01:25.789)
  ‚Ä¢ WEBVTT headers
  ‚Ä¢ [M√∫sica] sound effects
  ‚Ä¢ Duplicate words
  ‚Ä¢ Extra whitespace

Output: Clean, readable transcript text

## ‚úÖ Final Output Format

Success response:
{
  "videoId": "nxub8Bmia68",
  "language": "es",
  "text": "Clean transcript text...",
  "wordCount": 1250,
  "charCount": 6789,
  "status": "success",
  "source": "youtube_captions"
}

Ready for downstream AI processing!

## ‚ö†Ô∏è Language Priority Logic
1. Exact match: preferredLanguage (es, en, fr...)
2. Fallback: first available caption
3. Returns captionId, language, totalCaptions\n\nSmart selection preserves preferred language when available.

## ‚ùå Error Handling Path

When no captions available:
* Returns structured error response
* Includes videoId and language info
* Suggests Whisper AI fallback
* Graceful workflow termination
* Prevents silent failures.

data.details:
The IF node can be used to implement binary conditional logic in your workflow. You can set up one-to-many conditions to evaluate each item of data being inputted into the node. That data will either evaluate to TRUE or FALSE and route out of the node accordingly.

This node has multiple types of conditions: Bool, String, Number, and Date & Time.
